  "edge_hypothesis": "Choppiness Index (CHOP) measures whether a market is trending or ranging on a 0-100 scale. When CHOP drops below 38.2 (Fibonacci level), the market has definitively transitioned from congestion into directional movement. This is a fundamentally different transition-detection mechanism from Vortex (directional intensity), Ichimoku TK (median-price cross), or MACD (momentum acceleration). CHOP measures the market's structural tendency to chop — its decline signals regime change at the market-structure level. The dead choppiness_donchian_fade used HIGH CHOP (>61.8) for ranging entries — this spec uses LOW CHOP (<38.2) for trend-emergence entries, the opposite regime and logic. Supertrend direction gate determines which way the trend is going once CHOP confirms trending conditions exist.",
